	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>New chips are too fast?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This forum is pretty quiet recently, so I though I would share something with you.
<br />
<br />My flash cartridge had a very interesting bug, the CPLD chip was too fast! It would cause graphics corruption in certain games like Donkey Kong Country, and if I turned on the 'turbo bits' to speed up the chip it wouldn't work at all.
<br />
<br />My theory is the different logic level (its a 3.3v part thats 5v tolerant) and faster speed made it turn off the bus buffer and address decoder before the graphics chip was actually finished reading, like a hold time violation. 
<br />
<br />I fixed the problem 100% by soldering a 100pf cap from the cart's CEn to GND. I have heard of a similar problem with the PowerPak, so I wonder if this could help with that.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

